items.name: Contemporarie style interior design
items.description:
Contemporary style interior design is defined by its emphasis on simplicity, clean lines, and a minimalist approach. It reflects the current trends in design, making it fluid and evolving.

The color palette tends to be neutral, with shades of white, black, and gray being prevalent, often accented by bold and vibrant colors. The use of light is a crucial component, with large windows, glass doors, and ample artificial lighting to create a bright, airy feel.

Furniture in contemporary design is often sleek and low-profile, with simple, geometric shapes and minimal ornamentation. Comfort and functionality are key aspects, with modern materials like chrome, glass, stainless steel, and molded plastic frequently used alongside more traditional materials like wood and leather.

The contemporary style often includes open floor plans and an integration of indoor and outdoor living spaces. Decorative elements are typically subtle and purposeful, with an emphasis on modern art and innovative, sculptural pieces.

Overall, contemporary interior design is about the simplicity of form and space, providing a calm, uncluttered environment that expresses sophistication and a sense of the present.

  3. Fashion advice: Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v10 can be used in fashion advisory applications, where it can evaluate a user's ao dai image and recommend ao dai styles that complement their body shape, skin color, and personal preferences.

Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v10 brings convenience in recognizing and classifying traditional long Vietnamese ao dai, contributing to the exploration and preservation of Vietnam's traditional culture in the fashion industry.

Kitsch style interior design embraces the unconventional, the extravagant, and the over-the-top. It's characterized by its use of bold colors, whimsical patterns, and eclectic mix of elements that may traditionally be considered "tasteless" or overly sentimental.

The color palette for kitsch design is often vibrant and loud, featuring bright pinks, greens, blues, and yellows. Patterns and prints like florals, animal prints, and pop-art designs are frequently used and mixed in daring ways.

Furniture in kitsch design can be a wild blend of styles, periods, and materials, often with a nod to retro or vintage aesthetics. The pieces might be brightly painted or upholstered with unusual fabrics.

Decorative accessories play a big part in kitsch style. These can include anything from novelty lamps, quirky figurines, and pop culture memorabilia to velvet paintings, plastic flowers, and kitschy kitchenware.

Overall, kitsch style interior design is about breaking design rules, mixing eras and styles, and creating a space that is fun, flamboyant, and reflects a sense of humor and individuality. It's about celebrating the joy in the ordinary and the charm in the tacky.

Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v02 full style color is a version of a model designed for the recognition and classification of traditional long Vietnamese ao dai. This model has been developed to identify and categorize different styles of Vietnamese ao dai based on images. It can classify Vietnamese ao dai based on factors such as style, color, patterns, and other details.

Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v02 has been trained on a large dataset containing thousands of images of traditional long Vietnamese ao dai from various angles and styles. Through the training process, the model has learned important characteristics of Vietnamese ao dai and has the ability to recognize different patterns and classify them into corresponding labels.

With Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v10, you can utilize it in applications related to Vietnamese ao dai, such as:

  1. Ao dai classification: The model can determine the style, color, and patterns of Vietnamese ao dai based on images. This can support automated classification, sorting, and searching of ao dai in online stores or personal collections.

  2. Style suggestions: If you want to create a diverse collection of Vietnamese ao dai, the model can suggest different ao dai patterns based on an input image. This can help users explore and choose suitable ao dai styles according to their preferences and personal style.

  3. Fashion advice: Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v02 can be used in fashion advisory applications, where it can evaluate a user's ao dai image and recommend ao dai styles that complement their body shape, skin color, and personal preferences.

Model Lora aoDaiVietnameseLong_v02 brings convenience in recognizing and classifying traditional long Vietnamese ao dai, contributing to the exploration and preservation of Vietnam's traditional culture in the fashion industry.

items.name: Arterior - Digital Art Style
items.description:
This is a custom merge of a lot of different artsy models that I have been using a lot, so I finally decided to share it! Generates both SFW and NSFW images quite well.

It results in a modern digital art style, with subtle outlines and heavy shading. If you don't like that style, you might have difficulty getting this model to do what you want.

Good-To-Knows

Here are some thing to know/keep in mind about this model:

  • Keep your prompts short, or reduce CFG scale.

  • Use negative embeddings like EasyNegative (I haven't used it in sample images)

  • It is pretty good at nsfw prompts, but sometimes anatomy is comically exaggerated

  • You CAN technically make male characters with this... but why would you

Reasoning

I created this with a bunch of models, keeping certain things in mind for the models I used

  1. Must be good at backgrounds

  2. Must not look ultra photoreal

  3. Must look 'imperfect' in terms of features; not look 'too clean'

It's fairly unstable to be merged into anything else (believe me I've tried!), so I'm not sure how usable it will be as a merge ingredient, but great for generating images.

Updates:

  • v2: Added more details, overall image should be better

If you like this, check out my other models!

items.name: Futura lacylotus (natural look)
items.description:
My rating vs expectation: 93%

(See "about this version" for changes. Good level of likeness with this one. Flexibility is also good (although please see TIPS to produce best result). This is the final version.)

All TIs I make depict real adults. Please apply it with good judgement. If you're the model and want this removed reach out to me via link below. I welcome all criticisms and suggestions with curiosity. If you like my work, buy me a house:
https://ko-fi.com/futurafree

This TI was trained in sd1.5 base with 5 vectors, 25 images, 11960 steps, and 478 epochs. This was finetuned for epiCRealism evo3 and Realistic Vision V4.0, but may work on others.

TIPS:

  • MUST be the first word in the prompt for likeness and consistency.

    • Example: futuralacylotus11960v52, portrait of a woman, long dress etc.

    • Not: Portrait of futuralacylotus11960v52, etc.

  • Recommended weight:

    • (0.98-1.0)

  • Optional:

    • Positive: no makeup

    • Negative: (wet skin)

      • Negative: (wet skin)

  • I use adetailer for all images, with mediapipe_face_full, blank pos and neg, 1024x1024, inpaint mask blur: 20, inpaint noise strength: 0.45.

  • Again, prompt in adetailer is left blank most of the time; (*exception*: if Loras/Lycoris is used and has significant impact on the appearance of the model's face, copy paste pos prompt without Loras/Lycoris into adetailer).

  • Upscaler I use: 4x_NMKD-Siax_200k.

items.name: Desktop Graffiti
items.description:
There's something about a school desk that just invites you to draw on it: you've got pens and pencils to hand, you're bored, it doesn't belong to you, and there's all that empty space that simply needs to be filled. Relive rainy days and detentions from years gone by with this style LoRA: trained on real examples of wooden desks that have been transformed and enhanced by anonymous artists. This model will cover your generations in scribbles, doodles, scratches, slogans, and hearts.

Two versions of this model are available: one trained against the base SD1.5 model, and one trained against a specialised cartoon-style checkpoint. The former will work well with base SD1.5 and photorealistic checkpoints, the latter will work better for Western animation and anime style checkpoints.

items.name: RPGShadow
items.description:
This is a LoRA for creating SHADOWs for medieval rpgs. It does use the main trigger word rpgshadow to distinguish it from normal shadows. There is some variety in how it renders depending on checkpoint. The photosomnia and cyberrealistic checkpoints did a good job on the long range shots, but most all others were pretty interesting at closer ranges. That being said, there are long range, medium range, and close range trigger words available.

The images were created with hires.fx x2, denoising 0.23, 4x_foolhardy_Remacri upscaler

The trigger words for the model are the following:

blurry, blurry background, cloak, close range, from behind, glowing, glowing eyes, holding, hood, hood up, hooded cloak, humanoid form, long range, medium range, no eyes, reaching out, red eyes, rpgshadow, solo
